<p>A bus veered off a road and plunged down an embankment on a steep mountain pass in Limpopo province, northern South Africa, on Sunday [abcnews.go.com#1][ndtv.com#2]. Authorities reported at least 42 deaths and 49 injuries from the crash [abcnews.go.com#1][allafrica.com#3]. NDTV, citing the provincial transport minister, earlier put the toll at 38 and said the driver apparently lost control about 90 kilometres from the Zimbabwe border while the bus was traveling toward Zimbabwe [ndtv.com#2]. Survivors were taken for treatment, as emergency services responded at the scene [abcnews.go.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/x71l7LzhhAX4SUfo1tKgDZAeFOW8bvuk75zFq_Bcq7ptez9nBDgr0rV43H0Y_g1YDDG72msXVNVZaNXER_R_zH0hUW2jVnKQkeUtiJuXE-oxPAAyXIinVhZ2kHtb_0bI0Htp_tDZartOb4k' alt='ABC News placeholder image accompanying reports on the Limpopo bus crash' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Casualty figures: Officials reported at least 42 fatalities and 49 people injured, though an earlier count cited 38 deaths [abcnews.go.com#1][allafrica.com#3][ndtv.com#2].</li><li>Crash setting: The bus left the roadway on a steep mountain pass in northern South Africaâ€™s Limpopo province [abcnews.go.com#1][ndtv.com#2].</li><li>Likely cause: The driver apparently lost control about 90 km from the Zimbabwe border, according to provincial authorities [ndtv.com#2].</li><li>Route and destination: The bus was traveling toward Zimbabwe when the crash occurred [ndtv.com#2].</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Limpopo transport department: The driver apparently lost control about 90 km from the Zimbabwe border as the bus traveled toward Zimbabwe. (<a href='https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/south-africa-bus-crash-bus-travelling-to-zimbabwe-crashes-after-driver-loses-control-9444487#publisher=newsstand'>NDTV</a>)</li><li>South African authorities: A bus veered off a road and plunged down an embankment on a steep mountain pass in northern South Africa. (<a href='https://abcnews.go.com/Internat